❯ so should we resolve 3. One real issue found: same-VUE resource constraints   
that you mentioned above                                                        
                                                                                
● No — don't touch it. Here's the reasoning:                                    

  Why it doesn't actually matter:                                               
   
  Both HiGHS and CBC run presolve before solving. Redundant constraints (ones   
  implied by other constraints already in the model) are identified and removed
  during presolve. The constraint lam[(0,0)] + lam[(0,1)] <= 1 is trivially     
  dominated by the convexity equality Σ_c lam[(0,c)] == 1, and any competent
  solver's presolve eliminates it in microseconds. It never reaches the simplex
  or branch-and-bound engine.

  Why fixing it would add complexity for no gain:                               
   
  The fix would require _append_column to track which cells belong to columns of
   the same VUE and skip adding a new entry when the cell already has an entry
  from that same VUE. That's extra bookkeeping (a Set[Tuple[int,int]] per VUE to
   track "cells already claimed by this VUE") for a case the solver handles for
  free.

  When it would matter:                                                         
   
  Only if you were using a solver with no presolve, which isn't the case here.  
  Even then, the redundant constraints are trivially tight — they add zero
  computational work to simplex beyond the extra row in the matrix.             
                  
  The pre-existing question:                                                    
   
  The original code had the exact same behavior. The issue was there before we  
  touched anything — we didn't introduce it, and resolving it isn't part of the
  work we're doing (optimizing the rebuild).                                    
                  
  Leave it, move on.           